Happy Caturday from Sugar Ray! Born in December 2015, Sugar Ray (aka Ramone) was rescued from an apartment complex in SW Houston where his family moved away and forgot him. Everyone who meets this boy says he is one of the nicest cats they have ever seen. Sugar Ray loves being brushed and receiving belly rubs. After you have performed one of these duties, you will be rewarded with a nose kiss. Since he has been inside he has gained a little weight and definitely has plenty of belly to rub! Many people prefer kittens, but if you can open your heart to a two-year old, you will have many years of fun and love.
If you are interested in this fun boy, contact www.homelesspets.net
